ion with firefighters became buried and, seemingly, died.\n\n- S.A. Tawks, Misadventurous\n|\nWhatever you do will be insignificant, but it is very important that you do it.\n\n- Mahatma\n|\nSometimes the greatest storms bring out the greatest beauty… Life can be a storm, but your hope is a rainbow and your friends and family are the gold.\n\n- Steve\n|\nTear your heart out of your chest. And hand it to God. There is no other healing. I swear, there is no other healing.\n\n- Yasmin\n|\nThe pain you have gone through will give you the strength of character to come through it all, so long as you learn from what you have suffered then it was not suffering at all.\n\n- Stephen Richards, The Pain You Feel Today Is The Strength You Feel Tomorrow\n|\nWe can escape the commonplace only by manipulating it, controlling it, thrusting it into our dreams or surrendering it to the free play of our subjectivity.\n\n- Raoul"